parameters.name: DbId
parameters.description:
The ID of the database. The database can be a physical database or a logical database.

*   To query the ID of a physical database, call the [ListDatabases](~~141873~~) or [SearchDatabase](~~141876~~) operation.
*   To query the ID of a logical database, call the [ListLogicDatabases](~~141874~~) or [SearchDatabase](~~141876~~) operation.

parameters.name: OrderId
parameters.description: The ID of the data change ticket. You can call the [ListOrders](~~144643~~) operation to query the ID of the data change ticket.

parameters.name: PageNumber
parameters.description: The number of the page to return.

parameters.name: PageSize
parameters.description: The number of entries to return on each page.

parameters.name: Tid
parameters.description: The ID of the tenant. You can call the [GetUserActiveTenant](~~198073~~) operation to query the tenant ID.
